HSBC Confirms Talks on Possible Sale of Canadian Unit

-- B y   S e a n   B .   P a s t e r n a k
-- 
2011-09-06T16:05:27Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-06/hsbc-confirms-talks-regarding-possible-sale-of-canadian-unit.html
HSBC Holdings Plc (HSBA) ,  Europe ’s largest
bank, is in talks regarding a possible sale of the full-service
investment advisory division of its Canadian retail brokerage
business.  No decision has been made to proceed with a transaction,
HSBC Canada said today in a statement.  The Globe and Mail reported last month that HSBC was
considering offers for the unit, which manages more than C$30
billion ($30.3 billion) of investors’ money.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sean B. Pasternak in Toronto at 
 spasternak@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editors responsible for this story:
